<!--
VOICING PLAN — 4150 Let All Mortal Flesh Keep Silence (F major)
Key: F (1 flat: Bb). Modal character centers on Dm (vi).

Phrase 1 (mm.1-6): vi opening — "33" pattern, open spacing. LH D2-A2-D3,
  RH A3-D4. BbM7 in m.2 uses IVΔ voicing for richness. Am arpeggio m.3.
  Gm7/Am split in m.5 with paired moving notes, contrary motion hands.
  F cadence m.6 uses IΔ four-note LH for full resolution.

Phrase 2 (mm.7-12): Bb opening "43" 1st inv with passing-tone RH in m.7
  mirrors the melody's D-E-F-G ascent. Am substitute for A major in m.12
  keeps diatonic; light sustained RH C-E color against pedal.

Phrase 3 (mm.13-16): Harmonic sequence vi→ii→ii→iii. Arpeggio LH m.14.
  Full "334" LH in m.15 (climax approach). "333" iii7 in m.16 (pre-final tension).

Final phrase (mm.17-19): Full vi "334" climax m.17 with high RH. ii→I
  voice-leading in m.18 (Gm→F final cadence). Final m.19 all sustained.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Contrary motion: LH descends in m.6 (F2-bass), RH ascends in m.7.
- Common tone D held RH m.1→m.2→m.3 as anchor.
- Smooth ii→V in m.10 (G→F, D→C in LH thirds).
- Passing arpeggio in m.14 (G-Bb-D-F) creates melodic LH line.

TEXTURE ARC:
mm.1-3: Open, 2-voice RH, 2-voice LH — quiet entry
mm.4-6: Broader, 3-voice LH, split harmonies — building
mm.7-9: Parallel motion mirrors melody — engaging
mm.10-12: Contrary hands, Am suspension — tension
mm.13-16: Full 4-voice LH, "334" climax — peak
mm.17-19: Full chords converging to final vi cadence — resolution
-->
